added.title: A Stickier Situation
added.description: When Sticky Joe tries to clip his pet rat's nails, it leads to a wild adventure.

added.title: Winning a Golf Tournament Is the Solution to All of Life's Money Problems
added.description: After the T-Car is towed due to outstanding parking tickets, Robin has Cyborg enter a golf tournament for the cash prize.

added.title: Intro
added.description: Control Freak leads the Titans on a chase through various cartoon intro sequences.

added.title: Legendary Sandwich
added.description: The team goes on a series of epic quests in order to create the world's perfect sandwich.

added.title: Pie Bros
added.description: Beast Boy has to get a job at a pie shop to earn enough money to buy Cyborg a birthday gift, only his job interferes with being able to attend the actual party.

added.title: Driver's Ed
added.description: Robin is inadvertently the getaway driver for a bank robbery in the midst of his driver's ed exam.

added.title: Dog Hand
added.description: Raven's supervillain father comes to visit and the rest of the team thinks he's the coolest...until he steals their souls.

added.title: La Larva de Amor
added.description: The gang agrees to babysit Silkie but then loses him. Meanwhile, Silkie has a telenovela adventure south of the border.

added.title: Hey Pizza!
added.description: Beast Boy and Cyborg try their best to slow the pizza delivery boy so they can get free pizza.

added.title: Super Robin
added.description: Robin's wish comes true and he finally gets superpowers - but at what cost?

added.title: Laundry Day
added.description: When the gang bickers over whose turn it is to do chores, things quickly get out of control until their dirty uniforms grow a mind of their own and attack!

added.title: Ghostboy
added.description: Starfire mistakenly thinks she's killed Beast Boy, leading him to pose as a ghost and torment her.

added.title: Double Trouble
added.description: Cyborg and Beast Boy create clones of themselves to do their chores and the clones create more clones until the situation grows out of control.

added.title: The Date
added.description: Robin poses as Speedy to sabotage his upcoming date with Starfire.

added.title: Gorilla
added.description: Beast Boy takes over as Alpha male of the Titans when he is in Gorilla-mode and Robin has to figure out how to get back on top.

added.title: Girls' Night Out
added.description: When the guys plan a guys night out, Starfire drags Raven out on a wild adventure of their own.

added.title: You're Fired
added.description: Beast Boy gets fired from the team and the Wonder Twins take his place.

added.title: The Responsible
added.description: Gumball and Darwin babysit Anais "responsibly", whilst "irresponsibly" flooding the house.

added.title: The Dress
added.description: Gumball goes to school in a dress and becomes the darling of Elmore High.

added.title: The Third
added.description: Gumball and Darwin spice up their friendship by introducing a third best friend.

added.title: The Debt
added.description: Gumball resolves to save Mr Robinson's life during Elmore's Senior Talent Show.

added.title: The Kiss
added.description: Gumball is traumatised when accidentally kissed on the mouth by his Grandma JoJo.

added.title: The Pressure
added.description: Gumball tries to save Darwin from being kissed by a girl.

added.title: The Painting
added.description: Principal Brown tries to "fix" Gumball's dysfunctional family.

added.title: The Laziest
added.description: Gumball and Darwin challenge Dad to a "lazy-off."

added.title: The Ghost
added.description: Gumball must learn to say "no" when Carrie the Ghost uses his body against his will.

added.title: The Mystery
added.description: Gumball sets out to solve the mystery of who stuffed Principal Brown into his locker.

added.title: The Prank
added.description: Gumball and Darwin's harmless pranks on Dad spiral hopelessly out of control.

added.title: The GI
added.description: Gumball and Darwin's martial arts costumes make them a laughing stock at school.

added.title: The Party
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are invited to a high school party, and have to bring a date!

added.title: The Refund
added.description: Gumball and Darwin unsuccessfully attempt to get a refund for their computer game.

added.title: The Robot
added.description: Gumball discovers that Bobert is planning to take over his identity and replace him!

added.title: Itch to Explore
added.description: Craig's quest to map the entire Creek takes him and his friends into the treacherous Poison Ivy Grove.

added.title: You're It
added.description: A vicious game of tag wreaks havoc on the Creek, claiming Kelsey as the next it.

added.title: Jessica Goes to the Creek
added.description: When Craig and Jessica are locked out of the house, Craig has no choice but to bring his little sister to the Creek.

added.title: Escape from Family Dinner
added.description: There's a huge water balloon fight at the creek but Craig is stuck at home for a family dinner, unless he can escape.

added.title: Monster in the Garden
added.description: Craig is determined to catch the monster that has been wreaking havoc in Granddad's garden.

added.title: Dog Decider
added.description: Unable to make tough decisions, Craig decides to put his choices in the hands of a dog named Fred.

added.title: Bring Out Your Beast
added.description: Craig wants to play a popular card game, so he decides to borrow Bernard's vintage and valuable cards.

added.title: Lost in the Sewer
added.description: Craig agrees to help The Sewer Queen map the sewers, but he quickly finds himself in over his head.

added.title: The Future is Cardboard
added.description: The kids meet an eccentric Cardboard Creator that invites Craig to help finish his masterpiece.

added.title: The Brood
added.description: Craig's determination to get his granddad a cicada shell causes him, Kelsey and JP to become trapped in their stump!

added.title: Give Pizza a Chance
added.description: Rivals Buster and Plucky decide to throw an epic pizza party and are shocked to find out they're actually getting along while Babs and Sweetie get into their first roommate disagreement.

added.title: Extra, So Extra
added.description: Babs realizes Acme Loo's school paper has closed so she starts a new one with her pal Sweetie. But when Plucky starts a gossipy tabloid to compete against them, which paper will come out on top?

added.title: Tooney Ball Lights
added.description: Buster and Sweetie join the Tooney Ball team during Electives Week while Babs and Plucky tackle the basics in Anvils 101, leaving Hamton on a journey to fix his indecisiveness.

added.title: Save The Loo Bru
added.description: Buster meets his nemesis, Montana Max, and must apply a new lesson from Bugs about drag to keep the Loo Bru from demolition.

added.title: Prank You Very Much
added.description: It's Prank Week at Acme Loo and our pals get into escalating shenanigans trying to out prank their rival, Aqua Loo.

added.title: General HOGspital
added.description: Hamton gets into medical school but soon realizes it's not at all what he imagined. Buster desperately tries to find a way to bring his pal back to Acme Loo.

added.title: Soufflé, Girl Hey
added.description: Babs and Buster are excited to get college jobs, but can they stand the heat cooking for the school chef?

added.title: Tears Of A Clone
added.description: Buster finds a cloning machine at Wile E. Coyote's yard sale that he uses to make another Buster and Babs and Sweetie snag a time machine that they use to open a vintage clothing store.

added.title: The Prince and the Boasty Boar
added.description: In an attempt to win the hand of Princess Jezabel, Boaris Von Tusk stages a tournament to prove that he is the greatest warrior in all The Five Kingdoms. Prince Ivandoe takes part, of course, for no warrior is greater than he! But so too does a Masked Knight who not only wins but turns out to be... Jezebel herself! For Jezebel is nobody's prize!!!
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Blobby Princess
added.description: Princess Syllabob, the blobby daughter of Axalotly, King of the Deep, has been carried off by a gang of gulls and discarded on the forest floor. Prince Ivandoe and Bert happen upon her and agree to escort the Princess back to the lake before she dehydrates. Overcoming obstacles, including a swan-napping by Prince Svan, Ivandoe and Syllabob develop... well, a sort of... friendship?
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Prince and the Wise Wizard of Wisdom
added.description: Struck down by a poisonous turnip, Prince Ivandoe & Bert must seek a cure from the Wise Wizard of Wisdom. They set off, and along the way, they are joined by an equally desperate small-faced bear, a bunny-dragon, and a truly useless fairy. Once they reach the Wise Wizard however, they discover that he is a lot less wise and a lot more "sassy" than anyone could have predicted!
added.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
added.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

added.title: The Tree Stooges Save Christmas Part 1
added.description: The kids accidentally destroy Chef's decorated Christmas tree. Scared this means they've ruined his Christmas, they go on an epic mission to replace his holiday treasures.

added.title: The Tree Stooges Save Christmas Part 2
added.description: The kids accidentally destroy Chef's decorated Christmas tree. Scared this means they've ruined his Christmas, they go on an epic mission to replace his holiday treasures.

added.title: Me, My Elf, and I
added.description: Duncan tricks Chef into taking the class to the North Pole in order to remove his name from the naughty list.

added.title: Snow Way Out
added.description: Owen wants everyone to love his new snowsuit and envy him, but it's just not working out that way.

added.title: Chapter 1: The Legs
added.description: Susie must rely on Oscar and Hedgehog in unimaginable ways after a magic trick gone wrong.

added.title: Chapter 2: If I Only Had a Wand
added.description: Hedgehog reckons with her mother's disapproval of magic.

added.title: Chapter 3: See Bees? Gee! Bees!
added.description: Oscar heads to the Sasquatch Monastery in search of enlightenment.

added.title: Chapter 4: Pepper's Funeral
added.description: With help from Pepper, Susie is able to lay a special dream of hers to rest.

added.title: Chapter 5: The Hits
added.description: Barb and the Alien King take an eventful walk around the island.

added.title: Chapter 6: Miracle Rabbit
added.description: Oscar and Ramona run an errand on the moon.

added.title: Chapter 7: The Three Grrs
added.description: Oscar helps the aliens with a special jester ritual that happens once every fifty years.

added.title: Chapter 8: Go Get Our Girls
added.description: Hedgehog and Oscar search for the missing coven members.

added.title: Chapter 9: Storybook Susie
added.description: Susie details her travels around the world.

added.title: Chapter 10: The Last Witch
added.description: Hedgehog worries that she may be too little to make big witch decisions.

added.title: Chapter 11: The Metaphysical Reserve
added.description: Susie steps through a portal into another realm.

added.title: Chapter 12: Night's Pockets
added.description: Pajamas and Jimjams try to find Time.

added.title: Chapter 13: Jar Guard
added.description: Mildred's Friend tells a cautionary tale.

added.title: Chapter 14: Bear With Me
added.description: A surprise visitor arrives on Summer Camp Island.

added.title: Chapter 15: Croissant Moon
added.description: The magical creatures work together to send Mildred on a mission so they can have a special bedtime.

added.title: Chapter 16: Retrace Our Hooves
added.description: Susie makes contact in another realm.

added.title: Chapter 17: Meeting of Mounds
added.description: The Coven challenges The Cuties to an impromptu softball game.

added.title: Chapter 18: Swellington Boots
added.description: When a summer storm brews, the crew cozies up in the library.

added.title: Chapter 19: Weather Your Weather
added.description: Susie mulls over her past.

added.title: Chapter 20: It Takes Time
added.description: The island welcomes a new era.

added.title: Barb and the Spotted Bears Chapter 1: A Barb is Born
added.description: On the third day of the world, Barb tries to save the ferns from being eaten by the spotted bears. But the bears are only getting hungrier and hungrier - will Barb be able to stop the ferns from going extinct?

added.title: Barb and the Spotted Bears Chapter 2: Hot Milk and Careless Whispers
added.description: Barb tries to soothe the spotted bears with a dreamy invention, but soon finds herself outnumbered. Will Barb be able to even the playing field - or will she become the bears' next snack?

added.title: Barb and the Spotted Bears Chapter 3: Nightcap
added.description: Barb and the elves band together to protect the source of all magic from a pair of fiendish intruders. But will Barb be able to outsmart two rascals as old as the world itself?

added.title: Betsy and Ghost Chapter 1: Burps 'n Sighs
added.description: On the eve of Ramona's exile to Frozen Time, Susie tries to get rid of the sad memory of their relationship, but soon finds herself haunted by the past.

added.title: Betsy and Ghost Chapter 2: Boo Jeans
added.description: It's Betsy's first night on Summer Camp Island, and she's looking forward to a cozy evening in with a nice cup of tea. But when Alice convinces her to participate in an initiation ritual, Betsy gets lost in the woods.

added.title: Betsy and Ghost Chapter 3: There's A Racket In My Hope Chest
added.description: The witches search for Betsy - who doesn't want to be found. Can she learn to love being a witch as much as she loves being a ghost?

added.title: Susie and her Sister Chapter 1: Heathers
added.description: Susie's new little sister has a gift for magic, but it's causing problems for the community. Will Susie learn to accept that Mildred is more powerful, and will the townsfolk be able to accept the most powerful witch in the world?

added.title: Susie and her Sister Chapter 2: Hot Corn Girls
added.description: On her 15th birthday, Susie must prepare for her Gibbous Rite Ceremony. Will Mildred be able to keep her chaotic magic in check for just one day so Susie can become the full witch woman of her dreams?

added.title: Susie and her Sister Chapter 3: Mildred's Friend
added.description: Locked in a standoff with Susie over who will say sorry first, Mildred runs away to the woods and befriends a ghost. Will one of the McAllister sisters give in and apologize before the townsfolk run Mildred out of town?

added.title: Oscar and the Monsters Chapter 1: Unaccompanied Oscar
added.description: When Oscar isn't invited to Alexa's birthday party, Mortimer tries to make him feel better by telling him about a similar time in his life. Ever the glowworm, Oscar sneaks back in time to help a young Mortimer overcome the sad experience.

added.title: Oscar and the Monsters Chapter 2: Tiny Outburst Society
added.description: After discovering that young Mortimer doesn't have any friends, Oscar helps him start a new club on campus. But the monsters are forced to hide their newfound friendship from the school - and Stuart.

added.title: Oscar and the Monsters Chapter 3: Witches' Brew
added.description: Mortimer and the monsters must figure out how to send Oscar back to his own time, but the only person that can help is the foe of monsters everywhere: a witch. Will they all be able to work together to get Oscar back to Hedgehog?

added.title: The Babies Chapter 1: Breakfast Errands
added.description: Frustrated that he doesn't know his magical identity, Oliver convinces Susie to tell him by means of nonviolent protest. Not wanting anyone in her house, Susie takes Oliver on a series of errands to help him figure it out.

added.title: The Babies Chapter 2: Teacup Giant
added.description: Susie sends Alexa to the Fjords to train as a giant, but her small size causes her to lag behind. Will Alexa be able to fake it until she makes it - or are these boots too enormous to fill?

added.title: The Babies Chapter 3: Lem Is Nothing
added.description: After landing in trouble with Susie, Lem runs away to Frozen Time to hide at Ramona's but is soon sniffed out by the fearsome Jabberwock. Later, Lem must decide whose wrath is worse: that of the Jabberwock, or a very grumpy Suze.

added.title: Sea Bunnies
added.description: Oscar discovers an underwater portal. His return ticket? An errand for Susie.

added.title: Mushrumours
added.description: Alice suffers the consequences of accidentally spreading a rumor about mushrooms.

added.title: Breakfast Like Gene Kelly
added.description: Oscar attempts to make the breakfast of his dreams.

added.title: Spirit Balls
added.description: Susie and Ramona teach the witches how to make spirit balls.

added.title: Oscar & His Demon
added.description: Oscar works to overcome his fear of crossing a very scary bridge.

added.title: The Emily Ghost Institute for Manners and Magical Etiquette
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog go to a magical etiquette class.

added.title: Jeremiah
added.description: Oscar finds and cares for a magical root from Susie's yard.

added.title: Tomorrow's Bananas
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog get an unsettling glimpse into the future.

added.title: Shave a Little Off the Wheel
added.description: A mouse in heels befriends a rogue snowflake.

added.title: He's Just Not Here Right Now
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog encounter New Jersey's most famous piece of folklore.

added.title: Hark the Gerald Sings
added.description: Oscar confronts an age-old superstition.

added.title: Hall of Mooms
added.description: Hedgehog tries to get her broom back.

added.title: Pepper and the Fog
added.description: After the island gets covered in fog, Pepper attempts to make it to Susie's house.

added.title: Susie and Ramona Chapter 1: Susie's Ark
added.description: When Susie learns magic is beginning to disappear from New York, she tries to lead all the magical creatures to safety.

added.title: Susie and Ramona Chapter 2: Ghost Baby Jabberwock
added.description: Susie, Ramona, and Barb team up in frozen time to see what's threatening magic.

added.title: Susie and Ramona Chapter 3: Meet Me in Massachusetts
added.description: Susie and Ramona train a gaggle of witches until they have a full coven.

added.title: Susie and Ramona Chapter 4: Witches in the City
added.description: Ramona sends Susie back to New York in search of new magical creatures.

added.title: Puddle and the King Chapter 1: Honey Moondog
added.description: The King leaves Hedgehog and Oscar in charge of the kingdom while he and Puddle are away - their only duty is to carry out the Swan-Upping.

added.title: Puddle and the King Chapter 2: Royally Bored
added.description: Hedgehog and Oscar discover alien jesters who live under the floorboards of the castle.

added.title: Puddle and the King Chapter 3: All the King's Slides
added.description: Oscar, Hedgehog and Puddle must figure out what's wrong with the King when he orders the aliens to turn all the planet's sugar into salt.

added.title: Yeti Confetti Chapter 1: Don't Tell Lucy
added.description: Oscar has to distract Lucy while the Yetis prepare a surprise for her.

added.title: Yeti Confetti Chapter 2: The Yum Whisperer
added.description: Lucy and a young yeti named Fife argue about the right way to raise a litter of baby yetis they found.

added.title: Yeti Confetti Chapter 3: The Sherbet Scoop
added.description: Lucy decides to tell a story during a Yeti cloud-making ceremony about a Yeti Elder she doesn't know.

added.title: Yeti Confetti Chapter 4: Lucy's Instrument
added.description: Lucy goes to Yeti school to find her instrument.

added.title: Yeti Confetti Chapter 5: Where's the Confetti
added.description: When it doesn't snow on the final day of Yeti Confetti, a Yeti Elder blames Lucy. In order to prove she belongs Lucy tries to find a way to make it snow.

added.title: Meeting of the Minds
added.description: While Oscar helps Hedgehog find her wand, Susie tries to convince the Meeting of the Minds that Hedgehog isn't responsible enough for magic.

added.title: Ava's Yard Sale
added.description: To help Ava overcome stage fright, Hedgehog takes Ava's violin into her own hands, while Oscar calls in for some reinforcements.

added.title: Molar Moles
added.description: Oscar's fib about his last baby tooth alerts the Molar Mole Fraud Squad, and Hedgehog jumps to his defense at a kooky mole trial.

added.title: Tortilla Towel
added.description: After making Oscar's tortilla towel dreams come true, he and Hedgehog find that running a business is harder than they thought.

added.title: Acorn Graduation
added.description: Hedgehog endures her first magic lesson with Susie, while Oscar sets out to save her seat for a must-see event: Acorn Graduation!

added.title: Dungeon Doug
added.description: On a trip into the world of Dungeon Doug, Oscar and his dad find themselves on a father-son bonding mission.

added.title: Tub on the Run
added.description: While Hedgehog and Max scour the island in search of a missing tub, everyone is dying to know: are things weird between them?

added.title: Spotted Bear Stretch
added.description: On the eve of the Spotted Bear Stretch, Oscar and his pajamas are stuck at Susie's place as unwelcome house guests.

added.title: French Toasting
added.description: Lucy's suspicious behavior prompts Oscar and Hedgehog to investigate whether or not she's the kingpin of a secret society.

added.title: We'll Just Move the Stars
added.description: When an astrological mismatch threatens King and Puddle's wedding, Oscar and Hedgehog join them on a quest to ensure love conquers all.

added.title: Catacombs
added.description: Oscar, Hedgehog, Lucy, and Saxophone must return a yeti comb to its home to save the island from a really bad hair day.

added.title: Wild Hearts Can't Be Caboodled
added.description: Things get wonky when Oscar and Hedgehog use magic to get an edge on their fellow campers in the Rainbow Unicorn Badge contest.

added.title: The Later Pile
added.description: Hedgehog convinces Oscar to tackle an overdue errand -- but this time, Oscar's procrastination habit has spooky consequences.

added.title: Honeydew Hatch
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog enter Frozen Time to help Ramona grow time babies, but Ramona and Susie's broken friendship causes problems.

added.title: Light as a Feather
added.description: While Hedgehog braves her first witch coven sleepover, Oscar awaits a secret signal in case she needs to be rescued.

added.title: When Harry Met Barry
added.description: Faced with two potential husbands -- burly Harry and sensitive Barry -- Barb enlists Hedgehog and Oscar to help her weigh her options.

added.title: Oddjobs
added.description: Hedgehog and Oscar investigate problems at U.M.P.S. and meet the new intern, Oddjobs, who's a great friend but a terrible employee.

added.title: Tumble Dry Low
added.description: When Hedgehog's podcast blows up, she must decide whether to ride the wave of fame or stay true to her small but loyal fan base.

added.title: Just You and Me
added.description: The full moon finds Betsy withholding her big werewolf secret from Susie, who spends the night trying to figure out what her BFF is up to.

added.title: Glow Worm
added.description: While Hedgehog is off "werewolfing," a deflated Oscar has a therapy session with Shark that helps him realize the magic within him.

added.title: The First Day
added.description: Best friends Oscar and Hedgehog get dropped off at their first day at summer camp.

added.title: Monster Babies
added.description: Alice lures Oscar and his monster friends for a tea party, but only to turn the monsters into cute babies.

added.title: Chocolate Money Badgers
added.description: Oscar learns that he can earn merit badges that unlock prizes.

added.title: Saxophone Come Home
added.description: Oscar befriends a teenage Yeti.

added.title: Pajama Pajimjams
added.description: Oscar pretends to be a talking pair of pajamas named "Jimjams" to make his friend Pajamas happy.

added.title: Oscar & Hedgehog's Melody
added.description: Susie holds the annual talent show that has the rest of the campers competing to win.

added.title: Feeling Spacey
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog arrive on a planet that has no emotions.

added.title: Ghost the Boy
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog befriend a ghost who can't remember who he is.

added.title: Computer Vampire
added.description: Oscar finds a mysterious old video game in the library.

added.title: The Basketball Liaries
added.description: With the help from Basketball, Oscar makes an impressive shot that scores him a spot on the Gold League.

added.title: Popular Banana Split
added.description: Hedgehog and Max discover a tiny high school when they are accidentally shrunk by a science experiment.

added.title: Time Traveling Quick Pants
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog learn about a quicksand that lets them go back in time.

added.title: It's My Party
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog plan a surprise birthday party for Susie.

added.title: Moon Problems
added.description: The Moon gets sad when Oscar loses his friendship bracelet.

added.title: Monster Visit
added.description: The monsters get nervous when their Godmonster comes for a visit.

added.title: Ice Cream Headache
added.description: The campers get magical powers from the witches supply of magic ice cream.

added.title: Pepper's Blanket Is Missing
added.description: Pepper's blanket goes missing at a cabin sleepover.

added.title: Hedgehog Werewolf
added.description: Hedgehog gets bit by a cute puppy and is starting to act strange.

added.title: Mr. Softball
added.description: Susie challenges the campers to a game of softball to get out of doing a chore.

added.title: Fuzzy Pink Time Babies
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog learn how to stop time.

added.title: Director's Cut
added.description: Oscar receives a camcorder from his parents and sets out to prove to them the magic on the island is real.

added.title: I Heart Heartforde
added.description: Oscar, hedgehog and the other campers are excited to take a trip to the non-magical town of Heartforde.

added.title: Space Invasion
added.description: A visit from Puddle the alien tests the limit of Oscar's hosting skills.

added.title: Momsoon
added.description: Hedgehog gets a call during her radio show from someone who needs her help.

added.title: Sneeze Guard
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog must work with the witches to cure Alice's camp-threatening illness.

added.title: Susie's Fantastical Scavenger Hunt
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog must learn to exist without each other when they are put on different teams during a scavenger hunt.

added.title: Mop Forever
added.description: At Alice's dress-up party the campers are magically turned into their costumes.

added.title: Pajamas Party
added.description: When Pajamas starts to panic that Oscar will outgrow her, Oscar tries to help but things go awry.

added.title: The Soundhouse
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog discover a new structure on the island and become friends with its caretaker.

added.title: Puff Paint
added.description: Oscar's painting is unpopular so he goes on a journey of self-discovery.

added.title: Susie Appreciation Day
added.description: Hedgehog and Oscar find themselves trapped in Susie's cabin and must escape undetected.

added.title: Campers Above the Bed
added.description: Hedgehog finds a city underneath her bed as she looks for her missing diary.

added.title: Midnight Quittance
added.description: Ramona invites Hedgehog and Oscar to participate in a special holiday ritual.

added.title: The Great Elf Invention Convention
added.description: Oscar, Max, and Hedgehog do a favor for Barb the elf in exchange for some chips.

added.title: Twelve Angry Hedgehogs
added.description: Hedgehog wants to win the Golden Science Badge but runs into some unexpected competition.

added.title: Spell Crushers
added.description: Hedgehog tries to get over a crush so she can regain her focus on magic.

added.title: The Library
added.description: The campers spend a rainy day at the library.

added.title: A New Life
added.description: Apple and Onion both leave their homes and follow their dreams to the big city but things don't go quite to plan.

added.title: The Perfect Team
added.description: Onion worries his relationship with Apple is in jeopardy when a stray cat enters the picture.

added.title: Tips
added.description: Apple and Onion have to find a way to ride the Hot Air Balloon which is in their town for one day only.

added.title: Falafel's Fun Day
added.description: When Falafel decides to pack up and leave the city, Apple and Onion have to convince him to stay or they'll have to leave too.

added.title: 4 on 1
added.description: Onion's fear of crowds threatens his basketball team's success.

added.title: Hotdog's Movie Premiere
added.description: Apple and Onion square off against a no-nonsense security guard after they're banned from the premiere of their friend Hot Dog's new movie.

added.title: Apple's Focus
added.description: Apple decides to help Onion achieve his dream of competing on a baking show.

added.title: Lil Noodle
added.description: Apple and Onion must remain legit enough to be in their favorite rapper's music video.

added.title: Gyranoid of the Future
added.description: Apple and Onion are dead set on riding Gyranoid of the Future, the craziest roller coaster at the carnival.

added.title: Fun Proof
added.description: Apple and Onion want to become this week's "Most Fun People".

added.title: Whale Spotting
added.description: In order to see a rare whale, Apple and Onion have to become members of an exclusive club, but one of them doesn't quite have the chops.

added.title: Food Truck
added.description: The Bears open up a food truck after being disappointed by the food options available to them. In an effort to drum up business, they start selling their food to animals until the animals go a little crazy.

added.title: Chloe
added.description: Chloe spends time with the Bears in an effort to research them for an upcoming presentation. But when the Bears sneak a peek at her very dry report, the Bears decide to jazz it up with exaggerated facts about themselves and their lifestyle.

added.title: Everyday Bears
added.description: It's a normal day for the Bears. This means that Ice gets in a fight with a Roomba, Panda's life gets turned upside down when a mouse invades his room and Grizz gets stuck in a tree. You know, everyday stuff for a bear.

added.title: Burrito
added.description: Grizz likes Burritos. A lot. So much so that after a restaurant makes a Bear-Sized Burrito, Grizz can't bring himself to eat such a majestic work of art. He carries the burrito everywhere making it a new and increasingly smelly part of his life.

added.title: Primal
added.description: Have the Bears lost their survival instincts by living in the modern world? Grizz wants to know so he purposefully gets the Bears lost in the deep forest.

added.title: Nom Nom
added.description: When Nom Nom shows up on the Bears' doorstep, disheveled and deposed from his spot as cutest internet star ever after a recent meltdown, he enlists the Bears to help him regain his title.

added.title: Shush Ninjas
added.description: The Bears are fed up with the decay of etiquette at today's theaters. The Bears take it upon themselves to be the police of the theater, sneaking up like ninjas to shush people who ruin the movie for others with their bad manners.

added.title: My Clique
added.description: Chloe, a child prodigy, finds it difficult to connect with her much older classmates. The Bears take her under their wing and show her how to make great college friends.

added.title: Charlie
added.description: You know that one annoying friend who just can't get the hint? That's Charlie, and he's Bigfoot. The Bears meet him when Charlie signs up on a home-sharing website to spend a weekend with the Bears. Charlie is the worst possible house guest for the Bears and nearly destroys their house.

added.title: Brother Up
added.description: After Panda stumbles and accidentally scares a pack of wolves away in the process, the hierarchy of the Bears is disrupted. Suddenly, Panda has become the alpha bear, and he and Grizz have to deal with the consequences of an emotional Panda being the leader of the three Bears.

added.title: Occupy Bears
added.description: When the city plans to destroy the Bears' cave in order to make way for a new cell phone tower, Grizz and Panda must find evidence from their past that proves they have rights to their land. And in case that fails, Ice Bear protests and tries to sabotage the construction crew.

added.title: Laser Light Cannon
added.description: A magical comet hurtles toward Beach City, and Steven must dig through his father's collection of old junk, and the past, to find the weapon that can save the town.

added.title: Cheeseburger Backpack
added.description: A mission to the Lunar Sea Spire takes a treacherous turn, but Steven has packed his totally amazing Cheeseburger Backpack with anything they could ever need!

added.title: Together Breakfast
added.description: Steven tries to get the Gems to take part in his special breakfast tradition, but instead finds himself tumbling through the magical catacombs of the Crystal Gem's temple.

added.title: Frybo
added.description: Steven helps a Boardie kid with his grueling job by using a magical gem shard that can bring clothing to life.

added.title: Cat Fingers
added.description: Steven attempts to master the power of shape shifting, but can only shape shift his fingers into tiny cat heads.

added.title: Bubble Buddies
added.description: Steven looks like a hero when he forms a magic crystal bubble around himself to protect a girl he likes from danger, but then panics when he can't figure out how to turn the bubble off!

added.title: Serious Steven
added.description: Steven tries to prove himself to be a worthy Crystal Gem to Garnet while they navigate their way out of an ancient Gem maze.

added.title: Tiger Millionaire
added.description: Steven joins Amethyst in an underground wrestling league.

added.title: Steven's Lion
added.description: Steven makes friends with a magical lion, but can't quite tell why it likes him.

added.title: Arcade Mania
added.description: Steven takes the Crystal Gems to Funland Arcade where Garnet learns the allure of video games.

added.title: Giant Woman
added.description: During a mission to the Sky Spire, Steven tries to convince Amethyst and Pearl to fuse together and become a giant woman.

added.title: So Many Birthdays
added.description: So Many Birthdays: Steven learns that the Crystal Gems are thousands of years old and decides to make up for all the thousands of birthdays they've missed.

added.title: Lars and the Cool Kids
added.description: Steven and Lars get to hang out with the cool kids in town, but their teenage shenanigans get them into magical trouble.

added.title: Onion Trade
added.description: A boy trade between Steven and Onion escalates to epic proportions.

added.title: Little Homeschool
added.description: Welcome to Little Homeschool, a place on earth where Gems from all over the universe can come learn how to live together peacefully! But there's one Gem who refuses to attend.

added.title: Guidance
added.description: Amethyst has been helping Little Homeschool Gems find jobs on the boardwalk, but Steven isn't sure about her approach.

added.title: Rose Buds
added.description: Steven gets a surprise visit from some old friends, and an even more surprising introduction to some new ones.

added.title: Volleyball
added.description: Steven is determined to help Pink Diamond's original Pearl heal the scar on her face.

added.title: Bluebird
added.description: Steven questions the motives of a mysterious fusion that suddenly shows up at his house.

added.title: In Dreams
added.description: Steven's dreams start broadcasting onto his bedroom TV.

added.title: Bismuth Casual
added.description: Pearl invites Bismuth to the roller rink for a lesson on how to forge human relationships.

added.title: Together Forever
added.description: Connie has a really clear vision for her future. Steven wants to make sure he'll be a part of it.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: Steven visits a doctor for the first time.

added.title: Mr. Universe
added.description: Greg takes Steven on the road to find the origins of the Universe name.

added.title: Fragments
added.description: Steven heads to the woods to train with a powerful mentor.

added.title: Homeworld Bound
added.description: Steven heads to the Diamonds for advice on how to control his new powers.

added.title: I Am My Monster
added.description: Everything is not fine.

added.title: The Future
added.description: Steven is finally ready to move on.

added.title: Slumber Party Panic
added.description: Finn must keep his promise to Princess Bubblegum and cover up the zombie problem they've created.

added.title: Trouble in Lumpy Space
added.description: Finn and Jake try to go on a quest while protecting Tree Trunks.

added.title: Ricardio the Heart Guy
added.description: Finn becomes jealous of Princes Bubblegum's new suitor.

added.title: The Jiggler
added.description: Finn and Jake must figure out what's wrong with a creature.

added.title: Evicted!
added.description: Marceline shows up and informs that the tree fort was once hers and she wants it back.

added.title: Tree Trunks
added.description: Finn and Jake must take charge after the businessmen they've outsourced some of their work to go too far.

added.title: Business Time
added.description: Finn and Jake must travel to a far-off land to stop Jake from becoming permanently Lumpy.

added.title: My Two Favorite People
added.description: Jake tries to broker peace between Rainicorn and Finn.

added.title: Memories of Boom Boom Mountain
added.description: Finn gets caught up in trying to make everyone happy.

added.title: Wizard
added.description: Finn single-mindedly pursues the powers an old wizard offers him, until he learns that with great power comes, yeah yeah yeah, all that.

added.title: City of Thieves
added.description: Finn tries not to be corrupted by the City of Thieves.

added.title: The Witch's Garden
added.description: Jake loses his powers to a witch.

added.title: Ello Gov'nor
added.description: After watching a scary movie about a British Taxi, the guys have to help Rigby overcome his fears.

added.title: It's Time
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby get in a fight over Margaret, and Mordecai sends them traveling through time by destroying all the clocks.

added.title: Appreciation Day
added.description: By trying to change Benson's opinion of them, Mordecai and Rigby accidentally create lots of work for themselves.

added.title: The Power
added.description: Mordecai & Rigby find a mysterious keyboard that allows them to do anything they want, including accidently sending Benson to the moon.

added.title: Caffeinated Concert Tickets
added.description: Mordecai & Rigby make a deal with a Coffee Bean to help them stay awake to work major overtime to pay for concert tickets.

added.title: Death Punchies
added.description: Rigby learns an ultimate karate move and becomes the bully of the park.

added.title: Free Cake
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby throw Skips a surprise birthday party in order to get free cake.

added.title: Meat Your Maker
added.description: After Rigby causes the guys to get locked in a meat locker, he must get help from some hot dogs in order to get them out.

added.title: Grilled Cheese Deluxe
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby lie about being astronauts in order to cut in line at a restaurant.

added.title: The Unicorns Have Got to Go
added.description: In order to impress Margret and ask her out, Mordecai hangs with a bunch of punk Unicorns who say they can help him get his lady.

added.title: Prank Callers
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby try and prank the Master Prank Caller to be the best prank callers. The MPC sends them back to 1982.

added.title: Don
added.description: Rigby's estranged accountant brother comes back to help save the park from an audit. While everyone loves Don, Rigby wants nothing to do with him.

added.title: Rigby's Body
added.description: After Rigby eats an excessive amount of junk food, his body quits on him, leaving him a ghost-like consciousness. Mordecai and Skips must find his body before the day is over.

added.title: Mordecai and the Rigbys
added.description: After lying about having an awesome band, Mordecai and Rigby must get help from their future selves in order to learn how to play in time for the battle of the bands.

added.title: Stuck Up, Up and Away/Schoolhouse Rocked
added.description: Stuck Up, Up and Away: Bratty little Princess comes to town and wants to be a Powerpuff Girl. When she doesn't get what she wants, the girls will have to pay./Schoolhouse Rocked: The Gangreen Gang goes back to school at Pokey Oaks Kindergarten and become the school bullies. Since the girls can't fight in school, how can they stop them?

added.title: Just Another Manic Mojo/Mime for a Change
added.description: Just Another Manic Mojo: The Powerpuff Girls lose their baseball in Mojo's house, offering him the perfect opportunity to destroy these pesky superheroines if he can only get them to sit still./Mime for a Change: An accidental bleach spill turns Rainbow the Clown into the malevolent Mr. Mime. He proceeds to turn Townsville black and white and dead all over.

added.title: Buttercrush/Fuzzy Logic
added.description: Buttercrush: Buttercup falls for Ace, the leader of the Gangreen Gang. But when the gang exploits her infatuation to lure Blossom and Bubbles into danger, Buttercup shows them the real meaning of the word crush./Fuzzy Logic: Beastly bumpkin Fuzzy Lumkins goes wild in Townsville and only the Powerpuff Girls, with some help from a flying squirrel, can teach him to respect other people's property.

added.title: Boogie Frights/Abracadaver
added.description: Boogie Frights: The Boogie Man creates perpetual night by launching a huge disco ball to block out the sun. While evil creatures are dancing and destroying in the dark, the Powerpuff Girls plot to crash the ball./Abracadaver: Al Lusion, the old-time Townsville magician, pulls off his greatest stunt yet when he comes back from the dead as the zombie Abracadaver to haunt Townsville.

added.title: Bubblevicious/The Bare Facts
added.description: Bubblevicious: Bubbles is tired of people dismissing her as more sugar than spice. When she sets out to prove she's hardcore, she takes everyone by surprise, even Mojo Jojo./The Bare Facts: After Mojo kidnaps and blindfolds him, the Mayor has to rely on the girls' very different individual accounts of the crime to figure out exactly what happened.

added.title: Insect Inside/Powerpuff Bluff
added.description: Insect Inside: Vile villain Roach Coach has a plan to infest Townsville with an army of cockroaches! The girls overcome their squirms to squash Roach Coach's scheme and force him to bug off./Powerpuff Bluff: Three local hoods get new identities when they find grown-up-sized Powerpuff costumes inside Townsville Jail. They terrorize Townsville while the Mayor mistakenly sends the real girls to the slammer.

added.title: Octi Evil/Geshundfight
added.description: Octi Evil: The heinous Him toys with Bubbles' mind by speaking to her through Octi, her favorite stuffed animal. Following Him's orders, Bubbles picks a fight with her sisters that lands them all in a time-out./Geshundfight: The Amoeba Boys' ill-conceived plan to stand in Townsville Park all night in the rain leaves them with a nasty virus that's really something to sneeze at.

added.title: The Rowdy Ruff Boys
added.description: Mojo Jojo creates the ultimate weapons against the Powerpuff Girls, boy equivalents! Enter Butch, Boomer and Brick, The Rowdyruff Boys.

added.title: Uh, Oh, Dynamo
added.description: Worried about his little girls' safety, the Professor creates Powerpuff Dynamo, a state-of-the-art protection system, to help them in battle.

added.title: Escape from Monster Island
added.description: After Bubbles wins two tickets to see the girls' favorite band Sensitive Thugz, Blossom and Buttercup vie for her plus one. But when the Mayor's plane crashes on Monster Island, the girls must put aside their differences to save the day!

added.title: Princess Buttercup
added.description: When Buttercup starts spending a lot of time with her new friends, a group of bad-girl skaters called The Derbytantes, it seems the Powerpuff Girls are down to two, which delights Princess Morbucks, who wants to fill the empty slot.

added.title: The Stayover
added.description: After going overboard on the candy, Blossom and Buttercup wake up with no memory of last night and no idea where Bubbles is! They must piece together the events of last night and find Bubbles before the Professor gets back!

added.title: Painbow
added.description: When a mysterious rainbow causes everyone to become unnaturally happy, the Powerpuff Girls must find where it ends to save the day and return Townsville to normal.

added.title: Man Up
added.description: When Buttercup's aggression inadvertently allows villain Man-Boy to escape, she starts a new-age lifestyle in an effort to be more calm. But when Man-Boy returns to enact his revenge, Buttercup must embrace the balance between punching and hugging in order to defeat him.

added.title: Bye Bye, Bellum
added.description: The Mayor becomes dependent on the Powerpuff Girls after his assistant Ms. Bellum departs, leaving the girls so busy they accidentally hire the dangerous Bianca Bikini as his new assistant! When Bianca captures the Powerpuff Girls, the Mayor finds the tables turned and must rely on himself to help them.

added.title: Little Octi Lost
added.description: Buttercup steals Octi to teach Bubbles a lesson but ends up wanting to keep him for herself.

added.title: Strong Armed
added.description: When Bubbles breaks her arm and gets a powerful robotic cast, she must learn to stop being timid and embrace her smashy side to defeat the sleazy, sinister Pack Rat!

added.title: Power Up Puff
added.description: During a fight, both Buttercup and Bubbles are surprised to discover they've leveled up, leaving Blossom to wonder when or if she'll get new powers too.

added.title: Tiara Trouble
added.description: Bubbles' excitement over being a contestant in the Townsville Beauty, Talent and All-Around Flair pageant is ruined when Blossom and Buttercup become overbearing stage-sisters. But when a mysterious tiara causes trouble for the contestants, they realize there are bigger problems at hand.

added.title: The Wrinklegruff Gals
added.description: Sick of being the tiniest kids at their new school, the girls convince Professor Utonium to create a potion to make them older! Unfortunately, when they take too much, they become senior citizens and a prime target for Mojo Jojo!

added.title: Arachno Romance
added.description: After the girls feel slighted by the Professor when he gets a new girlfriend, the girls conspire to break them up.

added.title: Puffdora's Box
added.description: When Blossom gets overzealous with the spring cleaning, she accidentally unleashes a group of evil spirits.

added.title: Blue Ribbon Blues
added.description: When a famous scientist comes to the school, Blossom will stop at nothing to impress him at the Science Fair even if that means putting Townsville in danger!

added.title: Spoooooky Game
added.description: The gang's weekly board game night has been getting a little too competitive lately, so when Unikitty finds a spooky old board game that's clearly haunted, their desire to win gets turned upside down, but cursed or not, they'll be the first to the finish line!

added.title: Sparkle Matter Matters
added.description: Unikitty learns that boring, old Richard has never produced any happy Sparkle Matter ever, she cooks up a formula with Dr. Fox that will overload him with emotions! Now, he's making so much Sparkle Matter it's threatening to destroy the kingdom! Can Unikitty help Richard find emotional balance before all is lost?

added.title: No Day Like Snow Day
added.description: When a blizzard hits the town, Master Frown tries to ruin everyone's fun by pretending to be a magical snowman! But when he gets frozen inside, Master Frown must worry less about ruining everyone's good time and instead not turning into a Frown-sicle, while he's forced to experience the joys of the holiday season!

added.title: Action Forest
added.description: Hawkodile is the toughest action hero in the land, until his old rival shows up to take vengeance on him. Defeated and in need of help, Hawkodile must train Unikitty and the others into super muscle­y tough bros. And there's only one place unstoppable warriors are made, the Action Forest.

added.title: Kaiju Kitty
added.description: When a giant monster attacks the Unikingdom, the gang fights back with Dr. Fox's awesome new secret weapon: a massive mega robot! But after the threat is contained, Unikitty doesn't want to stop using the  awesome robot, so she finds excuses for them to use it for everything, no matter how pointless. But what if the greatest threat to the kingdom turns out to be them?

added.title: Fire & Nice
added.description: When Master Frown causes Unikitty to have an angry outburst that gets a little too destructive, she wishes her Rage Kitty side wasn't part of her anymore. Thanks to a new Dr. Fox invention, she gets her wish: Rage Kitty and Nice Unikitty split apart into two! But with Unikitty now unable to get angry, she learns bottling up your anger is never a good thing.

added.title: Kitchen Chaos
added.description: After a workplace injury, Richard is unable to do his servant work. Unikitty and the others take on the task of one simple chore, clean the kitchen. This incredibly boring task taxes our heroes as they find every way possible to not do it. Will they be able to accomplish this goal and bring Richard back?

added.title: Crushing Defeat
added.description: When Hawkodile develops a secret crush on Dr. Fox, he finds himself actually crushing down in size! With Hawkodile too embarrassed to tell her (or anyone) about it, Unikitty and the gang become his love gurus to help him confess his feelings before he shrinks away into nothing!

added.title: Wishing Well
added.description: When Puppycorn uses a wishing well and it doesn't come true, Unikitty is shocked to discover the reason: all the wishes made over the years can't be granted because they're trapped at the bottom of the well (it's a dumb system.) She frees them to bring joy to the town… only to discover that they've gone a little bad after years trapped in a dark hole. Soon, they wish it would end!

added.title: Hide N' Seek
added.description: Unikitty is proud to be the reigning champ of Hide N' Seek Day. But when Unikitty finds everyone in the kingdom except for Richard, she hunts him down at all costs. Will Richard continue to elude the Princess at her favorite game, and if so, how?!

added.title: Stuck Together
added.description: When Master Frown's head is stuck on Unikitty's butt, she vows to help him get his own body back, but first, she has to attend to her nice princess duties! But sharing a body with Master Frown can get pretty complicated, especially when Master Frown has his own agenda.

added.title: Little Prince Puppycorn
added.description: Puppycorn finally realizes he's a prince, so he wants to be in charge of the kingdom for once! Despite their friends' concerns, Unikitty makes Puppycorn ruler but realizes absolute power in the hands of the pup is too much for him to handle and his ideas aren't exactly great. Can they remove him from power while keeping the kingdom from revolting?

added.title: Pet Pet
added.description: Unikitty and the gang bring home a tiny creature they name Pet Pet, but Richard won't let them keep it if they can't prove they are responsible owners. But when Pet Pet runs away, Unikitty must pretend to be Pet Pet until they can find him, or Richard will never let them have Pet Pet (or any pet) ever again! Will Unikitty survive pet training, or finally admit responsibility is a lot harder than she thought?

added.title: Kitty Court
added.description: When Unikitty has a little auto incident with Master Frown, he insists on taking it to court! Frown's thrilled. There's nothing worse than boring old court and he can't wait to subject Unikitty to it! Unikitty is happy to make things right but the trial will be in Unikitty Court, which is so nonsensical and fun. It's Frown's worst nightmare! Will Master Frown succeed in bumming Unikitty out? Or will he be the one punished by their legal antics?

added.title: Fun Dungeon Face Off
added.description: Clarence's Mom treats Clarence, Jeff and Sumo to an afternoon at Rough Riders Chicken, a fast food restaurant with a play emporium. When Clarence and Sumo steal Jeff's fries, Jeff is forced to confront his germ phobias head-on in the restaurant's seemingly unsanitary play area.

added.title: Money Broom Wizard
added.description: Can Clarence, Jeff and Sumo manage to have a good time at "Pizza Swamp" Arcade with only one dollar to spend between them? Yes.

added.title: Lost in the Supermarket
added.description: During a trip to the supermarket with his mom, Clarence discovers produce adventure and coupon intrigue in aisle five...and every other aisle.

added.title: Clarence Gets a Girlfriend
added.description: When Clarence is asked out on a date by Ashley, a girl in his class, he realizes he doesn't know the first thing about having a girlfriend! Clarence enlists Sumo and Jeff to transform himself into the perfect gentleman just in time for his big date.

added.title: Dinner Party
added.description: When Clarence's mom takes Clarence to a stuffy dinner party, Clarence embarks on a quest for fun wherever it can be found.

added.title: Honk
added.description: Seeking to improve his communication skills, Clarence turns to a squeeze horn. It's really annoying.

added.title: Dollar Hunt
added.description: Clarence hosts a fun "dollar hunt" game to meet new friends. But things go awry when Clarence accidentally buries the money his Mom gave him to buy refreshments for her book club meeting.

added.title: Zoo
added.description: Clarence and Belson make a true odd couple when they're paired up during a field trip to the zoo and find themselves locked inside after hours.

added.title: Man of the House
added.description: Clarence's first night home alone spirals out of control, forcing Clarence and his pals to wage war against their own home security measures.

added.title: Puddle Eyes
added.description: A nap in mud seals Clarence's eyes and leaves him sightless, potentially dooming his team's chances in the school's ill-conceived "Vision Bee."

added.title: Dream Boat
added.description: Sumo devotes himself to the Sisyphean task of building a boat, defying the expectations of everyone in his life, including himself.

added.title: Belly Bros
added.description: When a kid is bummed that his favorite shirt won't fit over his big belly, it's up to Uncle Grandpa to show him that t-shirts come and go, but having a big belly is always cool.

added.title: Tiger Trails
added.description: In the final moments of helping a kid, Uncle Grandpa just needs his trusty Giant Realistic Flying Tiger, but when he finds out she's gone, it sends UG on a journey to find the tiger and figure out why she left.

added.title: Space Emperor
added.description: When UG mistakes a kid in a costume for an evil space emperor, he sends him to another dimension where he becomes an actual evil space emperor and UG must figure out some way to bring him home.

added.title: Funny Face
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa accidentally unleashes a floating Funny Face that's so funny you laugh yourself to insanity, the guys realize that only Gus' seriousness can save them, but will he help them after they've hurt his feelings?

added.title: Moustache Cream
added.description: When UG and the gang are in a rush to purchase some emergency moustache cream, they face a formidable foe: Mart Mart.

added.title: Nickname
added.description: When a kid wants a cool nickname, UG tells him he has to earn it in the most legendary way ever: yard work!

added.title: Driver's Test
added.description: When a girl has trouble passing her driving test, Uncle Grandpa shows up to help her.  But when they accidentally set a Crazy Baby loose in the city, it's up to Uncle Grandpa to stop it... by teaching the girl how to drive!

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Sitter
added.description: Gus and Pizza Steve have plans to go out for the night, but UG can't be left alone in the RV, so they need a babysitter.  But when none are available, they turn to UG to babysit himself.

added.title: Afraid of the Dark
added.description: When UG helps a little girl who is afraid of the dark, he convinces her there's nothing to be afraid of but their imaginations.  But when their imaginations prove to be pretty terrifying, they go on a quest to turn on the lights.

added.title: Treasure Map
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang don't have money to pay for their meal at a restaurant.  But when they discover a treasure map, it could be the answer to all their problems.  Too bad the treasure map is actually a restaurant activity placemat.

added.title: Locked Out
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa gets locked out of his RV and accidentally sets off the security system, it's up to him and his friends to disarm it before it destroys them.

added.title: Jorts
added.description: When Mr. Gus gets stuck in an embarrassingly super tight pair of jorts, he has to somehow get out of them in order to save his friends.

added.title: Brain Game
added.description: Uncle Grandpa calls on Pizza Steve, the self-proclaimed master of video games, to help a kid beat a game.  Only problem: Pizza Steve is terrible at video games.

added.title: Grocery Store Friend
added.description: While helping Duane at the supermarket, Jessica meets a new friend and has trouble staying focused on her responsibilities.

added.title: Glow Toy
added.description: When Jessica can't get a new toy to work, she learns a new way to appreciate it.

added.title: Bedtime Routine
added.description: Jessica wants to be a big kid and get ready for bed all on her own, but she can't remember everything in her routine.

added.title: Small Uncle's Big Bath
added.description: When Jessica discovers her favorite toy is dirty she volunteers to give him a bath.

added.title: The Big Kid Playground
added.description: Jessica goes in the big kid part of the playground for the first time, and befriends Stanleigh.

removed.title: Loose Change
removed.description: Sylvester is upset when Granny paints the bedroom but he learns the importance of change.

removed.title: Yours, Mine...and Mine, Mine!
removed.description: Daffy thinks if he shares his old toys, Granny will buy him all new toys.

removed.title: Act Your Age
removed.description: The kids try to see who can act most like a baby, while vying for Granny's attention.

removed.title: The Waiting Game
removed.description: Bruno and Nia are tasked with teaming up to help someone very special to the savvy brake car -- a mechanic! But when Bulstrode and his wrench shipment are delayed, it sends Bruno into an agitated tail-spin. To soothe their friend, the engines decide to pass the time by playing the ultimate Waiting Game and learning how to have fun while daydreaming, anticipating, and practicing patience!
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Pouting Match
removed.description: Lola tries pouting to get what she wants, and soon all the babies are doing it.

removed.title: Wishbone
removed.description: The Titans make wishes on a wishbone, but when it's broken, they must travel to Gobble-Gobble Land to set things right.

removed.title: The Prince and the Sing-Songy Stag
removed.description: When Prince Ivandoe valiantly sets free Brian the Bard, he discovers he is now stuck with him... until such time that Brian saves Prince Ivandoe's life in return. This would not be so awful if Brian didn't send all day singing accurate, yet deeply unflattering, songs about Prince Ivandoe's looks and abilities.
removed.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

removed.title: Wise Quacker
removed.description: Melissa gets laughs doing hurtful impressions of the other kids, but she takes the jokes too far.

removed.title: The Prince and the Tears of Triumph
removed.description: In an effort to impress Jezebel the thiefstress, Prince Ivandoe and Bert set off to find the elusive Centicore. For the Magic Tears of the Centicore are rumored to cure all known ailments. But how exactly does one make a massive mountain-goat, made from stone, blub?
removed.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

removed.title: The Prince and the Chicken of Doom
removed.description: A fire-breathing Giant Chicken is destroying the local farmers' prize vegetables. Prince Ivandoe vows to capture the Giant Chicken, but... gets captured by her instead. He seems to bring out her maternal side, and she in turn reminds him of Nanny. So when an angry mob attacks, Ivandoe heroically jumps to his Giant Nanny-Chicken's defence.
removed.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
removed.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

removed.title: The Prince and the Turnip Tricksters
removed.description: Prince Ivandoe vows to capture the turnip thief... the very worst type of thief! Prince Ivandoe and Bert are guided by some suspiciously Germanic woodland characters towards an old cabin. It turns out to be an elaborate trap, devised by the Sassy Gnomes, to punish Ivandoe for his inconsiderate turnip-top littering.
removed.seriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe
removed.originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

removed.title: The Prince and the Swoony Swanstress
removed.description: Prince Ivandoe and Bert take a lovely, but lost and confused, Swanstress under their wing. When finally, her memory returns, it turns out she is none other than the awful Princess Svandelyne, stuck-up sister to Prince Svan - Prince Ivandoe's greatest nemesis! And when Svan turns up, well, this can only end up in a Prince-Off. And does!

removed.title: The Prince and the Valiant Quest
removed.description: Prince Ivandoe and Bert set off on their heroic quest and, almost immediately, a winged serpent steals their map to Eagle Mountain. But that shan't stop a plucky young buck and his devoted squire from fulfilling their destiny. With the assistance of a quite staggeringly incompetent Dwarf called Alan, a new sword is forged and the Quest continue-eth!
